                    <msContents>
                        <summary>
                            The <title xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc" key="work_1605" change="#ids-cleanup">Rawz̤at
                                al-shuhadā'</title> (Garden of Martyrs) recounts various hardships and calamities endured by
                                prophets, saints, and martyrs and by the first Shi‘ite Imam <persName key="person_34436377" ref="http://viaf.org/viaf/34436377/" type="standard" role="subject" change="#role-assignment #ids-cleanup">ʻAlī ibn Abī Ṭālib (ca. 600–661)</persName> and his family,
                            particularly Imam <persName ref="http://viaf.org/viaf/89661385/" key="person_89661385" role="subject" change="#role-assignment">Ḥusayn ibn ʻAlī (d. 680)</persName>.
                        </summary>
